data.description: This country home sits on .665 lush acres. It has a large enclosed porch to enjoy summer evenings with outside access to the garage way and entry to the kitchen. The kitchen is large and has an oversized laundry that opens to a mud room to an enclosed entryway on the west side. The home also features a front  enclosed entry / mudroom to remove those wet boots before accessing the living room. Make this you home workshop and space to play, garden and have all your toys. Fruit trees are waiting for you to make that prize apple pie. A 25x 14' attached work shop is great for your projects. An additional small shed will house your garden tools. A  10x18' carport type shelter can shelter your side by side or tractor. The ditch runs on the east side providing a bit more h20 for an ample sized garden from the GEM VILLIAGE LAND OWNERS AND WATER USERS ASSOSIATES. At this time fees are 20/year. The home has a historic well. RV friendly. An oversized 1 car garage plus storage accesses the home by a covered open Breezeway and walkway between the home and Garage. located in Gem Village Between Bayfield and Durango makes for an easy trip for supplies and entertainment. Natural forest and an outdoor playground  will challenge the adventurous. Priced to sell this home won't last!
